          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>1 fol.; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: KFQ 30; Lines per page: 19; Dimensions: 120 x 175 mm; Qurʾānic Text: Q 28:7-32; Script style: kūfī E; Estimated date of production: 800-1000.</p>
              <p>Cf. entry by François Déroche about fragment KFQ 30 (Déroche, <ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/QJQEKNSJ" sameAs="QJQEKNSJ" type="zotero">The Abbasid Tradition, London 1992</ref>, p. 117): "63 / Single folio / End oft he 9th century AD or 10th / 12 x 17.5 cm, with 19 lines to the page / <hi rend="italic">Material</hi> Parchment; the recto is the hair side / <hi rend="italic">Text area</hi> 8.5 x 14.5 cm / <hi rend="italic">Script</hi> Style E, with <hi rend="italic">mashq</hi> / <hi rend="italic">Accession no</hi>. KFQ 30 / This folio contains <hi rend="italic">Sūrat al-qaṣaṣ</hi> (XXVIII), verses 7-32. The text is written in brown ink, seemingly without diacritical marks. Red dots indicate the vocalization. Verses are not punctuated, but a red circle (I.A.I) marks the end of every tenth verse. On the recto, red marks left by the surah title written on the preceding folio can be seen. The lower left-hand corner has been lost.”</p>
            </summary>
